<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="624" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d624">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17701</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of War</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-31">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Secretary of War presents his compliments to the Honorable. The
                            Secretary of State, and encloses for his information copy of telegram
                            just received from the Commanding General, Southern Department.</p>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure—Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Funston</persName>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Adjutant General</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">,<placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort Sam Houston</hi></placeName>,
                                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-30">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1172. Following just received from General Bell: “I saw General
                                Gavira at 10.30 this morning. He had not at that time received
                                instructions from his Government regarding shipment of supplies by
                                Mexican Northwestern but at once sent a telegram and stated he would
                                let me know as soon as he heard.”</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Funston</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>